comment: Allen (MEM) maintains legal guarding position and Westbrook (OKC) falls to the ground.

A player who falls and slides with the ball only travels if he gains an advantage. Here, with little defensive pressure, Westbrook (OKC) gains no advantage by sliding and calls a timeout anyway. RHH shows trip is self-inflicted.
After communicating with the Replay Center, the ruling on the court that Conley's (MEM) field goal was a 3 point attempt was upheld.
Allen (MEM) makes contact to Westbrook's (OKC) body that causes him to fall to the ground when he reaches in for the steal.
Westbrook (OKC) makes contact with Gasol's (MEM) wrist and causes him to lose control of the ball.
Westbrook (OKC) commits a take foul on Chalmers (MIA).

Westbrook (OKC) kicks his leg into Gasol (MEM) on his shot. An offensive player commits a foul when he seeks contact with an airborne defender in a legal guarding position if the contact is not incidental to the shot, as here, and/or he dislodges the defender.
Adams (OKC) commits a take foul on Green (MEM).
Adams (OKC) commits a take foul on Chalmers (MEM).

Westbrook (OKC) plants and establishes his left foot as his pivot foot as he gathers the ball. He then raises his pivot foot off the floor, but passes prior to returning the pivot foot to the floor, which is legal.
